-- 3i Group Shareholders Suggest Liquidation, Sunday Times Reports
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2012-04-01T10:39:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-01/3i-group-investors-suggest-liquidation-sunday-times-reports.html
Some investors in  3i Group Plc (III)  have
suggested the private-equity company consider selling all its
assets and then shut down, the  Sunday Times  reported, without
identifying the shareholders.  One investor suggested the London-based company find a
buyer, according to the newspaper. Kathryn van der Kroft, a
spokeswoman for London-based 3i, declined to comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Martin in London at 
